    <h2 class="mb-3">Minesweeper Rules</h2>

    <p class="mb-3">
        Minesweeper is a logic puzzle where you must clear a minefield without detonating any mines. 
        Players reveal cells, and numbered cells indicate the number of mines adjacent to them. 
        The goal is to flag all mine locations and open all safe cells.
    </p>

    <h4 class="mb-2">Rules:</h4>
    <ul class="text-start d-inline-block text-left">
        <li><strong>Board:</strong> The game board consists of a grid of cells.</li>
        <li><strong>Mines:</strong> Mines are randomly scattered throughout the grid.</li>
        <li><strong>Opening Cells:</strong> Clicking a cell reveals its content.</li>
        <li><strong>Number Clues:</strong> Indicates number of adjacent mines (including diagonals).</li>
        <li><strong>Flagging Mines:</strong> Right-clicking a cell flags it as a potential mine.</li>
        <li><strong>Chording:</strong> If adjacent flags match number, clicking reveals surrounding cells.</li>
        <li><strong>Winning:</strong> Flag all mines and open all safe cells.</li>
        <li><strong>Losing:</strong> You lose if you click on a mine.</li>
    </ul>

    <h4 class="mt-4 mb-2">Tips:</h4>
    <ul class="text-start d-inline-block text-left">
        <li><strong>Start with Corners:</strong> Reveal edge numbers first.</li>
        <li><strong>Deduction:</strong> Use numbers to figure out safe cells.</li>
        <li><strong>1-2-1 Pattern:</strong> Learn common patterns to predict mines.</li>
        <li><strong>Chord When Possible:</strong> Use chording to clear areas faster.</li>
        <li><strong>Avoid Guessing:</strong> Rely on logic, not chance.</li>
        <li><strong>Look for Patterns:</strong> Recognize layouts like “1-1”, “1-2-1”, etc.</li>
        <li><strong>Be Patient:</strong> Think before you click. Minesweeper rewards careful moves.</li>
    </ul>
</div>
